Meta: _elementor_data:
[{"id":"1358743c","elType":"container","settings":[],"elements":[{"id":"f8f2e3b","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<h2 style="text-align: left;" data-start="189" data-end="250"><span style="font-size: 24pt;">Essential Fire Safety Solution for Immediate Fire Control</span></h2><p style="text-align: left;" data-start="252" data-end="549">A Fire Extinguisher Blanket is a critical fire safety device designed to suppress small fires and protect individuals from flames. Manufactured from high-performance, fire-resistant materials, our fire blankets provide a fast, effective, and maintenance-free method of fire control in emergency situations.</p><p style="text-align: left;" data-start="551" data-end="659">Available in 1x1 Meter and 2x1 Meter sizes to suit residential, commercial, and industrial environments.</p><h3 style="text-align: left;" data-start="666" data-end="685"><span style="font-size: 18pt;">Product Overview</span></h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-start="687" data-end="936">Fire blankets work by smothering flames and cutting off the oxygen supply, making them ideal for controlling cooking fires, electrical fires, and clothing fires. Easy to deploy and safe to use, they are an essential addition to any fire safety plan.</p><h3 style="text-align: left;" data-start="943" data-end="961"><span style="font-size: 18pt;">Available Sizes</span></h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-start="963" data-end="987"><strong>1x1 Meter Fire Extinguisher Blanket</strong></p><ul style="text-align: left;" data-start="988" data-end="1131"><li data-start="988" data-end="1054"><p data-start="990" data-end="1054">Recommended for homes, kitchens, vehicles, and small offices</p></li><li data-start="1055" data-end="1094"><p data-start="1057" data-end="1094">Compact design for convenient storage</p></li><li data-start="1095" data-end="1131"><p data-start="1097" data-end="1131">Effective for small fire incidents</p></li></ul><p style="text-align: left;" data-start="1133" data-end="1157"><strong>2x1 Meter Fire Extinguisher Blanket</strong></p><ul style="text-align: left;" data-start="1158" data-end="1349"><li data-start="1158" data-end="1245"><p data-start="1160" data-end="1245">Suitable for commercial kitchens, factories, workshops, and industrial facilities</p></li><li data-start="1246" data-end="1295"><p data-start="1248" data-end="1295">Provides wider coverage and enhanced protection</p></li><li data-start="1296" data-end="1349"><p data-start="1298" data-end="1349">Ideal for larger fire risks and personal protection</p></li></ul><h3 style="text-align: left;" data-start="1356" data-end="1371"><span style="font-size: 18pt;">Key Features of Fire Extinguisher Blanket</span></h3><ul style="text-align: left;" data-start="1373" data-end="1662"><li data-start="1373" data-end="1431"><p data-start="1375" data-end="1431">Manufactured from high-quality fire-resistant fabric</p></li><li data-start="1432" data-end="1466"><p data-start="1434" data-end="1466">Withstands high temperatures</p></li><li data-start="1467" data-end="1510"><p data-start="1469" data-end="1510">Quick-release pull tabs for immediate use</p></li><li data-start="1511" data-end="1543"><p data-start="1513" data-end="1543">Lightweight and easy to handle</p></li><li data-start="1544" data-end="1603"><p data-start="1546" data-end="1603">Supplied in a durable wall-mounted pouch or container</p></li><li data-start="1604" data-end="1642"><p data-start="1606" data-end="1642">No servicing or maintenance required</p></li><li data-start="1643" data-end="1662"><p data-start="1645" data-end="1662">Long service life</p></li></ul><h3 style="text-align: left;" data-start="1669" data-end="1684"><span style="font-size: 18pt;">Applications</span></h3><ul style="text-align: left;" data-start="1686" data-end="1909"><li data-start="1686" data-end="1710"><p data-start="1688" data-end="1710">Residential kitchens</p></li><li data-start="1711" data-end="1737"><p data-start="1713" data-end="1737">Restaurants and hotels</p></li><li data-start="1738" data-end="1774"><p data-start="1740" data-end="1774">Offices and commercial buildings</p></li><li data-start="1775" data-end="1813"><p data-start="1777" data-end="1813">Industrial and manufacturing units</p></li><li data-start="1814" data-end="1868"><p data-start="1816" data-end="1868">Educational institutions and healthcare facilities</p></li><li data-start="1869" data-end="1909"><p data-start="1871" data-end="1909">Vehicles and emergency response kits</p></li></ul><h3 style="text-align: left;" data-start="1916" data-end="1937"><span style="font-size: 18pt;">Usage Instructions</span></h3><ol style="text-align: left;" data-start="1939" data-end="2244"><li data-start="1939" data-end="2004"><p data-start="1942" data-end="2004">Pull the tabs to release the fire blanket from its container</p></li><li data-start="2005" data-end="2064"><p data-start="2008" data-end="2064">Hold the blanket in front of you to protect your hands</p></li><li data-start="2065" data-end="2129"><p data-start="2068" data-end="2129">Carefully place the blanket over the fire to fully cover it</p></li><li data-start="2130" data-end="2178"><p data-start="2133" data-end="2178">Switch off the heat source if safe to do so</p></li><li data-start="2179" data-end="2244"><p data-start="2182" data-end="2244">Allow the blanket to remain in place until completely cooled</p></li></ol><h3 style="text-align: left;" data-start="2251" data-end="2287"><span style="font-size: 18pt;">A Reliable Choice for Fire Safety</span></h3><p style="text-align: left;" data-start="2289" data-end="2515">Our <a href="https://afsfireball.com/">AFS</a> Fire Extinguisher blankets provide dependable protection and rapid response during fire emergencies. With simple operation and proven effectiveness, they are an essential safety solution for both personal and professional environments.</p><p data-start="2517" data-end="2615"> </p><p style="text-align: left;" data-start="2517" data-end="2615"><strong>Available Sizes:</strong> 1x1 Meter | 2x1 Meter<br data-start="2555" data-end="2558" /><strong>Application:</strong> Fire suppression and personal protection</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":false},{"id":"e01db61","elType":"container","settings":{"flex_direction":"column"},"elements":[{"id":"6a17b23","elType":"widget","settings":{"title":"FAQ","header_size":"h3","align":"center","_padding":{"unit":"px","top":"20","right":"20","bottom":"20","left":"20","isLinked":true}},"elements":[],"widgetType":"heading"},{"id":"b29d81e","elType":"widget","widgetType":"nested-accordion","settings":{"items":[{"item_title":"What exactly is a fire extinguisher blanket?","_id":"fc3fbef"},{"item_title":"How does a fire extinguisher blanket work?","_id":"6975cc2"},{"item_title":"Where should I keep my fire extinguisher blanket at home?","_id":"d0c4984"},{"item_title":"Can I use the fire extinguisher blanket on cooking fires?","_id":"9f2170e"},{"item_title":"Is a fire extinguisher blanket better than a regular fire extinguisher?","_id":"0066281"},{"item_title":"Can children or elderly family members use it?","_id":"12a1498"},{"item_title":"How big is a typical fire extinguisher blanket?","_id":"ed20403"},{"item_title":"Can I reuse a fire extinguisher blanket once it’s been used?","_id":"87ecead"},{"item_title":"Will it leave a mess like a chemical fire extinguisher?","_id":"b030fa9"},{"item_title":"Can the fire extinguisher blanket protect a person?","_id":"215781b"},{"_id":"402bf27","item_title":"What are the limits of a fire extinguisher blanket?"},{"item_title":"Does it work on electrical fires?","_id":"81c54cc"},{"item_title":"How do I inspect or care for my fire extinguisher blanket?","_id":"7027bb4"},{"item_title":"Can I install the fire extinguisher blanket on a wall?","_id":"4367608"},{"item_title":"What materials are used in a fire extinguisher blanket?","_id":"ccab5a2"},{"_id":"0202bc3","item_title":"Does it help with grease splashing or oil fires?"},{"_id":"523009a","item_title":"When should I not attempt to use a fire extinguisher blanket?"},{"_id":"bc585e5","item_title":"Should a fire extinguisher blanket be part of my home safety plan?"}],"title_typography_typography":"custom","title_typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":16,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[{"id":"d46d6fd","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"item #1","content_width":"full"},"elements":[{"id":"f45062b","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p data-start="533" data-end="888">A <em data-start="448" data-end="475">fire extinguisher blanket</em> is a specially designed fire-resistant sheet made from materials like fiberglass that smothers small fires by cutting off their oxygen supply. It’s simple, chemical-free, and ideal for quick response in kitchens, workshops, garages, and homes.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"31eb13b","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"item #1","content_width":"full"},"elements":[{"id":"238d560","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>It works by suffocating the fire — when you place the blanket over a small flame, it blocks oxygen (one leg of the “fire triangle”), stopping combustion. This is effective before fires grow out of control.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"feb5aa1","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"item #1","content_width":"full"},"elements":[{"id":"3910253","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p data-start="1334" data-end="1393">Keep it in easily accessible places where fires are most likely to start, like near the stove in the kitchen, next to a BBQ grill, in the garage, or by your electrical panel. Dry, visible storage helps ensure fast access.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"4df3a02","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"item #1","content_width":"full"},"elements":[{"id":"c384c7d","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p data-start="1721" data-end="1955">Yes — kitchen grease or small stovetop fires are exactly the kind of incident a fire blanket is designed for. However, make sure the fire is still small and contained before using this method.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"22686dd","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"item #1","content_width":"full"},"elements":[{"id":"9999467","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>They serve different purposes. A fire extinguisher blanket is great for small, contained fires (especially in kitchens), while a traditional extinguisher covers wider fire types and larger areas. Most safety experts recommend having both.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"a665421","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"item #1","content_width":"full"},"elements":[{"id":"a5980b4","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>Absolutely. One benefit of a fire extinguisher blanket is that it’s easy to use — no complex levers or nozzles, just unfold and cover the fire. It’s intuitive even under stress.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"480de49","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"item #1","content_width":"full"},"elements":[{"id":"48f5bbd","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p data-start="2373" data-end="2585">Sizes vary, but many practical home blankets are around 1 m × 1 m — large enough to cover a pot flame, pan fire, or small electrical sparks safely. Larger sizes are also available for bigger risks.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"af25b19","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"item #1","content_width":"full"},"elements":[{"id":"b5a7dc6","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>No — once deployed in a fire event, a fire extinguisher blanket should not be reused. The material can be weakened or damaged and may not perform correctly again. Always replace it after any use.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"6f95792","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"item #1","content_width":"full"},"elements":[{"id":"7b27ac8","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>Good news — no messy powders or chemicals. A fire extinguisher blanket silences flames without leaving residue, making cleanup much easier.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"b748cc4","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"item #1","content_width":"full"},"elements":[{"id":"43279bf","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p data-start="3369" data-end="3587">Yes — in some situations, you can wrap a person to shield them from small flames or heat while evacuating. This isn’t its primary use, but in emergencies, it’s a useful protective cover.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"267a019","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"Item #11"},"elements":[{"id":"cb852f1","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>They shouldn’t be used for large, fast-spreading fires, fires involving accelerants (like gasoline), chemical fires, or where flames are above ground level. In these cases, evacuation and professional firefighting tools are safer.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"7fc5ec5","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"Item #11"},"elements":[{"id":"e530439","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p data-start="3868" data-end="4107">If the power is <em data-start="3884" data-end="3907">completely turned off</em>, a fire blanket can help. However, electrical fires are tricky — it’s safer to disconnect the electricity first or use equipment designed for electrical fires.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"35b23e9","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"Item #11"},"elements":[{"id":"983f174","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>Check it regularly for tears, holes, or moisture damage. Store it dry and away from UV exposure. Do not wash or fold it harshly — damage can reduce effectiveness. If the blanket is compromised in any way, replace it.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"3b85b9c","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"Item #11"},"elements":[{"id":"bcb058d","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>Many insurance companies recognize fire safety readiness when assessing property risk profiles. Installing a fire extinguisher combo kit enhances your safety infrastructure, potentially contributing to lower premiums or easier compliance with policy requirements. Always check with your insurance provider for applicable guidelines.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"8b9524f","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"Item #11"},"elements":[{"id":"ae82d7b","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>Most are made with fire-resistant fiberglass or similar materials that can withstand high heat without catching fire or melting.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"e348fc1","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"Item #16"},"elements":[{"id":"f939bfe","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>Fire blankets are useful for small pan fires, but grease can be unpredictable — if the grease is splashing or fire is spreading, stay safe and let professional responders handle it. Training is key.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"e50fff1","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"Item #17"},"elements":[{"id":"9b548e2","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>Don’t use it if the fire is large, producing heavy smoke, or spreading fast, or if you can’t safely approach it. In those cases, prioritize calling emergency services.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true},{"id":"d9e4120","elType":"container","settings":{"_title":"Item #18"},"elements":[{"id":"952dd01","elType":"widget","settings":{"editor":"<p>Yes — experts and fire safety guides recommend having a fire blanket as part of a broader fire safety strategy, especially in kitchens and homes with frequent cooking. They are simple, effective for small fires, and complement other tools like smoke alarms and extinguishers.</p>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"text-editor"}],"isInner":true,"isLocked":true}]},{"id":"0f1272d","elType":"widget","settings":{"html":"<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "What exactly is a fire extinguisher blanket?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "A fire extinguisher blanket is a specially designed fire-resistant sheet made from materials like fiberglass that smothers small fires by cutting off their oxygen supply. It’s simple, chemical-free, and ideal for quick response in kitchens, workshops, garages, and homes."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "How does a fire extinguisher blanket work?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "It works by suffocating the fire — when you place the blanket over a small flame, it blocks oxygen (one leg of the “fire triangle”), stopping combustion. This is effective before fires grow out of control."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Where should I keep my fire extinguisher blanket at home?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Keep it in easily accessible places where fires are most likely to start, like near the stove in the kitchen, next to a BBQ grill, in the garage, or by your electrical panel. Dry, visible storage helps ensure fast access."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Can I use the fire extinguisher blanket on cooking fires?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Yes — kitchen grease or small stovetop fires are exactly the kind of incident a fire blanket is designed for. However, make sure the fire is still small and contained before using this method."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Is a fire extinguisher blanket better than a regular fire extinguisher?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "They serve different purposes. A fire extinguisher blanket is great for small, contained fires (especially in kitchens), while a traditional extinguisher covers wider fire types and larger areas. Most safety experts recommend having both."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Can children or elderly family members use it?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Absolutely. One benefit of a fire extinguisher blanket is that it’s easy to use — no complex levers or nozzles, just unfold and cover the fire. It’s intuitive even under stress."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "How big is a typical fire extinguisher blanket?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Sizes vary, but many practical home blankets are around 1 m × 1 m — large enough to cover a pot flame, pan fire, or small electrical sparks safely. Larger sizes are also available for bigger risks."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Can I reuse a fire extinguisher blanket once it’s been used?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "No — once deployed in a fire event, a fire extinguisher blanket should not be reused. The material can be weakened or damaged and may not perform correctly again. Always replace it after any use."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Will it leave a mess like a chemical fire extinguisher?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Good news — no messy powders or chemicals. A fire extinguisher blanket silences flames without leaving residue, making cleanup much easier."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Can the fire extinguisher blanket protect a person?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Yes — in some situations, you can wrap a person to shield them from small flames or heat while evacuating. This isn’t its primary use, but in emergencies, it’s a useful protective cover."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "What are the limits of a fire extinguisher blanket?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "They shouldn’t be used for large, fast-spreading fires, fires involving accelerants (like gasoline), chemical fires, or where flames are above ground level. In these cases, evacuation and professional firefighting tools are safer."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Does it work on electrical fires?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "If the power is completely turned off, a fire blanket can help. However, electrical fires are tricky — it’s safer to disconnect the electricity first or use equipment designed for electrical fires."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Can I install the fire extinguisher blanket on a wall?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Yes, it’s best to mount the blanket near likely fire spots so it’s easy to grab. Many models come with a quick-release pouch that hangs on a wall or cabinet."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "How do I inspect or care for my fire extinguisher blanket?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Check it regularly for tears, holes, or moisture damage. Store it dry and away from UV exposure. Do not wash or fold it harshly — damage can reduce effectiveness. If the blanket is compromised in any way, replace it."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "What materials are used in a fire extinguisher blanket?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Most are made with fire-resistant fiberglass or similar materials that can withstand high heat without catching fire or melting."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Does it help with grease splashing or oil fires?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Fire blankets are useful for small pan fires, but grease can be unpredictable — if the grease is splashing or fire is spreading, stay safe and let professional responders handle it. Training is key."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "When should I not attempt to use a fire extinguisher blanket?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Don’t use it if the fire is large, producing heavy smoke, or spreading fast, or if you can’t safely approach it. In those cases, prioritize calling emergency services."
    }
  },{
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": "Should a fire extinguisher blanket be part of my home safety plan?",
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": "Yes — experts and fire safety guides recommend having a fire blanket as part of a broader fire safety strategy, especially in kitchens and homes with frequent cooking. They are simple, effective for small fires, and complement other tools like smoke alarms and extinguishers."
    }
  }]
}
</script>"},"elements":[],"widgetType":"html"}],"isInner":false}]
